{"kind":"symbol","variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/bytes"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/BytesProtocol","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper"],"type":"conformsTo","title":"Conforms To","kind":"relationships"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Bytes"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Bytes","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"content":[{"anchor":"overview","type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The purpose of a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GBytes"},{"type":"text","text":" is to keep the memory region that it holds"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"alive for as long as anyone holds a reference to the bytes.  When","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the last reference count is dropped, the memory is released. Multiple","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"unrelated callers can use byte data in the "},{"code":"GBytes","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" without coordinating","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"their activities, resting assured that the byte data will not change or","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"move while they hold a reference."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"code":"GBytes","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" can come from many different origins that may have"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"different procedures for freeing the memory region.  Examples are"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"memory from [func"},{"code":"GLib.malloc","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"], from memory slices, from a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"[struct","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MappedFile","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"] or memory from other allocators."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"code":"GBytes","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" work well as keys in [struct"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/HashTable","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":"]. Use","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.Bytes.equal"},{"type":"text","text":"] and [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.Bytes.hash"},{"type":"text","text":"] as parameters to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.HashTable.new"},{"type":"text","text":"] or [func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.HashTable.new_full"},{"type":"text","text":"]."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GBytes"},{"type":"text","text":" can also be used as keys in a [struct"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Tree","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":"] by passing the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"[method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.Bytes.compare"},{"type":"text","text":"] function to [ctor"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.Tree.new"},{"text":"].","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The data pointed to by this bytes must not be modified. For a mutable"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"array of bytes see [struct"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ByteArray"},{"type":"text","text":"]. Use"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.Bytes.unref_to_array"},{"type":"text","text":"] to create a mutable array for a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GBytes"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"sequence. To create an immutable "},{"code":"GBytes","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" from a mutable","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[struct"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ByteArray","isActive":true},{"text":"], use the [func","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.ByteArray.free_to_bytes","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"]"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"function."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Bytes","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" type acts as a reference-counted owner of an underlying "},{"code":"GBytes","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"It provides the methods that can operate on this data type through "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/BytesProtocol","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" conformance.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Bytes"},{"text":" as a strong reference or owner of a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GBytes"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"name":"Note","type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/BytesRef","isActive":true},{"text":" (instead of ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Bytes","isActive":true},{"text":") for a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GBytes"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"note"}],"kind":"content"}],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"role":"symbol","symbolKind":"class","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text